article.description: Christina Wirth scored 16 points to lead No. 21 Vanderbilt to a 92-37 victory over Lipscomb on Saturday.
article.headline: No. 19 Vandy holds Lipscomb to school-record low point total
article.linkText: Lipscomb sets school low in loss to Vanderbilt
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Christina Wirth scored 16 points to lead Vanderbilt (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) to a 92-37 victory over Lipscomb on Saturday.

Lipscomb's point total was the lowest in school history. The Lady Bisons shot only 23.5 percent from the field and were only 3-for-20 from behind the arc.

Merideth Marsh and Jennifer Risper added 13 points each for the Commodores (9-3). Katie Rollins led the Lady Bisons (2-10) with eight points.

Vanderbilt made eight of its first 10 shots to race to a 19-2 lead. Lipscomb made only four of its first 20 shots and shot 21.4 percent from the field in the first half.

The Commodores grabbed their first 30-point lead at 41-11 with 4:04 left in the first half on a basket and free throw by Liz Sherwood.

Shooting woes continued in the second half for the Lady Bisons, who scored their first basket at the 11:33 mark. By then, the Commodores had built a 68-21 lead and later led by 58 points.
